description._content: Catalog #: 09_01772 Title: Frederick A. Hoover Special Collection Photo Pearl Harbor Hawaii Additional Information: Navy personnel. Handwritten inscription ""VIP's in Warrant Officers Mess off Pearl Harbor. 26 May 1952"", Frederick A. Hoover was the 100th individual to receive his aviator license (June 8th 1912). He performed stunts in air shows and was known as 'The Death Cheating Aviator"". He was a member of the Early Birds of Aviation. Tags: Frederick A.
